VALUES
(43, 6, 6, 1, 22, 1, 1, NULL, 'Testing of Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of testing faith in both passages. In John 6:6, Jesus tests Philip''s faith, while in Genesis 22:1, God tests Abraham''s obedience.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 6, 5, 13, 3, 3, NULL, 'Testing Faith and Loyalty', 'This connection highlights the theme of God testing individuals to reveal their faithfulness. Both passages emphasize the idea of proving one''s love and commitment to God through challenges.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 6, 14, 32, 31, 31, 'to prove him', 'Testing of the Heart', 'This connection highlights the theme of testing one''s heart and intentions. Both passages emphasize the idea of being tried to reveal what is within, as seen in the phrases about proving and trying.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 6, 5, 8, 16, 16, NULL, 'Testing and Provision in Wilderness', 'This connection highlights the theme of testing and provision in both passages. John 6:6 mentions proving, while Deuteronomy 8:16 discusses how God tested the Israelites to do them good.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 6, 5, 33, 8, 8, 'to prove him', 'Testing and Proving Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of proving individuals in faith. Both passages emphasize the act of testing, with John referencing a direct test of faith and Deuteronomy recalling a historical test of the Levites.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 7, 4, 11, 21, 22, NULL, 'Provision and Sufficiency in Need', 'This connection highlights the theme of questioning sufficiency in the face of large needs. Both Philip and Moses express doubt about the ability to provide enough food for a vast number of people.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 7, 41, 6, 37, 37, 'two hundred pennyworth of bread', 'Connection of Bread and Cost', 'Both passages emphasize the cost of bread needed to feed the crowd. The mention of ''two hundred pennyworth of bread'' in both verses highlights a shared concern about providing sufficient food.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 7, 43, 12, 5, 5, 'two hundred pennyworth of bread', 'Connection of Monetary Values', 'Both passages emphasize monetary amounts related to food and charity. Philip mentions ''two hundred pennyworth'' for bread, while Judas questions the value of ''three hundred pence'' for ointment, highlighting the theme of resource allocation for the needy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 7, 12, 4, 43, 43, 'not sufficient for them', 'Provision for Many', 'Both passages emphasize the insufficiency of resources to feed a large crowd. In John 6:7, Philip notes that two hundred pennyworth of bread is not enough, while in 2 Kings 4:43, the servitor questions the adequacy of food for a hundred men. This connection highlights the miraculous provision that follows in both accounts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 7, 40, 18, 28, 28, 'pennyworth', 'Connection of Monetary Value', 'Both passages emphasize monetary amounts, with ''pennyworth'' in John and ''pence'' in Matthew. This connection highlights the theme of debt and provision in the context of financial transactions.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 8, 40, 4, 18, 18, 'Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother', 'Connection of Andrew and Peter', 'This connection highlights the relationship between Andrew and Peter, as both passages mention Andrew as Simon Peter''s brother. The mention of Andrew in John 6:8 reinforces his identity as a disciple and brother of Peter, who is introduced in Matthew 4:18.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 8, 43, 1, 40, 44, 'Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother', 'Andrew''s Role in Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize Andrew''s identity as Simon Peter''s brother and his role in bringing others to Jesus. In John 1:40-44, Andrew first finds Simon Peter, while in John 6:8, he is mentioned as a disciple, highlighting his ongoing involvement in the ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 12, 4, 42, 44, 'five barley loaves', 'Miraculous Provision of Food', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous provision of food from limited resources. In each case, a small amount of barley is multiplied to feed a large group, demonstrating God''s ability to provide abundantly despite initial doubts.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 40, 14, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Loaves and Fishes', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of five loaves and two fishes. This connection highlights the disciples'' acknowledgment of limited resources in the face of a large crowd.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 41, 6, 38, 38, 'five barley loaves, and two small fishes', 'Connection of Loaves and Fishes', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''five loaves'' and ''two fishes'' as the resources available for feeding a large crowd. This connection highlights the miraculous nature of the feeding event in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 42, 9, 13, 13, NULL, 'Feeding the Multitude Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''five loaves and two fishes'' as insufficient for the large crowd. This connection highlights the miraculous nature of the feeding events in both accounts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 19, 78, 19, 19, NULL, 'Provision in the Wilderness', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s ability to provide sustenance in seemingly impossible situations. In both passages, there is a questioning of God''s provision, with the lad''s meager food and the inquiry about a table in the wilderness reflecting doubt in divine sustenance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 40, 16, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Loaves and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the significance of the ''five loaves'' in both passages. In John, the lad''s offering is questioned, while in Matthew, the disciples are reminded of the miracle involving the same loaves, emphasizing their lack of understanding.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 9, 41, 8, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Feeding Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous feeding of large crowds using limited resources. The mention of ''five loaves'' in both verses highlights the significance of the number in the context of abundance from scarcity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 10, 42, 9, 14, 16, NULL, 'Feeding the Five Thousand', 'Both passages emphasize the number of men present, about five thousand, and the command to make them sit down. This connection highlights the miraculous feeding event that is central to both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 10, 40, 14, 18, 19, NULL, 'Feeding the Multitude Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the command to have the multitude sit down on the grass before the miracle of feeding occurs. This connection highlights the organization of the crowd and the setting for Jesus'' miraculous provision.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 10, 40, 15, 35, 36, 'Make the men sit down', 'Feeding the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the command to ''sit down'' before the miraculous feeding occurs. This connection highlights the organization of the crowd in preparation for the distribution of food.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 10, 41, 6, 39, 41, 'Make the men sit down', 'Feeding the Five Thousand', 'Both passages emphasize the command to make the men sit down, highlighting the organization of the crowd before the miracle of feeding. The mention of ''green grass'' in both accounts further connects the setting of this miraculous event.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 10, 41, 8, 6, 7, 'Make the men sit down', 'Feeding the Multitude', 'This connection highlights the act of Jesus commanding the people to sit down before performing a miracle of feeding. Both passages emphasize the organization of the crowd and the miraculous provision of food.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 43, 6, 23, 23, 'given thanks', 'Connection of Thanksgiving in John', 'Both passages emphasize the act of giving thanks by Jesus. In John 6:11, Jesus gives thanks before distributing food, while John 6:23 references this act of thanksgiving in relation to the bread eaten.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 52, 5, 18, 18, 'given thanks', 'Thankfulness in Action', 'This connection highlights the act of giving thanks in both passages. In John 6:11, Jesus gives thanks before distributing food, while 1 Thessalonians 5:18 emphasizes giving thanks in all circumstances.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 40, 15, 36, 36, NULL, 'Miraculous Feeding of Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus taking loaves and fishes, giving thanks, and distributing them through his disciples to the crowds. This connection highlights the miraculous nature of Jesus'' provision in feeding large groups of people.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 45, 14, 6, 6, NULL, 'Thanksgiving in Eating', 'Both passages emphasize giving thanks while eating. In John 6:11, Jesus gives thanks before distributing food, while Romans 14:6 highlights that eating should be done with gratitude to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 42, 24, 30, 30, NULL, 'Connection of Bread and Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus taking bread, blessing it, and distributing it. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' actions in providing sustenance and fellowship.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 11, 9, 9, 13, 13, 'given thanks', 'Blessing Before Eating', 'This connection highlights the act of blessing before a meal. In both passages, the act of giving thanks or blessing precedes the distribution of food to the people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
